  "text": "The Kafka producer record flow begins when user code creates a ProducerRecord and calls KafkaProducer.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java:829). This delegates to KafkaProducer.doSend() (line 941) which serializes the key and value, then calls RecordAccumulator.append() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:275) to add the record to a batch for the target partition.\n\nRecordAccumulator.append() either appends to an existing batch via ProducerBatch.tryAppend() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/ProducerBatch.java:144) or creates a new batch with RecordAccumulator.appendNewBatch(). Once records are accumulated, the Sender thread periodically calls Sender.runOnce() which invokes Sender.sendProducerData() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:357).\n\nSendProducerData() first checks which batches are ready to send by calling RecordAccumulator.ready() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:763). This method iterates through topics via RecordAccumulator.partitionReady() (line 643) which checks each partition's batches using RecordAccumulator.batchReady() (line 603) to determine readiness based on batch fullness, linger time, and other factors via ProducerBatch.isFull() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/ProducerBatch.java:492).\n\nOnce ready nodes are identified, RecordAccumulator.drain() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:954) is called to extract batches for those nodes. Drain collects batches for each node by calling RecordAccumulator.drainBatchesForOneNode() (line 847), which dequeues batches from partition queues if they satisfy readiness conditions.\n\nThe drained batches are then sent to the network. Sender.sendProduceRequests() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:856) iterates through the batches and calls Sender.sendProduceRequest() (line 864) for each node, building a ProduceRequest and queuing it via NetworkClient.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:541). NetworkClient.send() delegates to NetworkClient.doSend() (line 551) which builds the request and finally calls Selector.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/network/Selector.java:391) to perform the actual network I/O operation."
}

